    "body": "```rust\ninitializing the kernel page table\nfinish linear mapping, mapping physical range: 0xffff800000000000 - 0xffff800008000000\nfinish metadata mapping\nfinish kernel code mapping, kernel code virtual address range: 0xffffffff80000000 - 0xffffffff81000000\nfinish kernel page table initialization\nerror: multiple definitions of symbol `__ostd_main`\n   --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:142:14\n    |\n142 |     unsafe { __ostd_main() };\n    |              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ error occurred here\n    |\nhelp: it's first defined here, in crate `init`\n   --> /home/zjp/KMiri/tests/init/src/lib.rs:7:1\n    |\n  7 | #[ostd::ktest::miri_main]\n    | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nhelp: then it's defined here again, in crate `osdk_test_kernel`\n   --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/osdk/deps/test-kernel/src/lib.rs:88:1\n    |\n 88 | #[ostd::ktest::miri_main]\n    | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n    = note: stack backtrace:\n            0: ostd::boot::start_kernel\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:142:14: 142:27\n            1: ostd::arch::boot::miri_boot\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/arch/miri/boot/mod.rs:73:14: 73:28\n            2: miri_start\n                at src/main.rs:18:5: 18:34\n    = note: this error originates in the attribute macro `ostd::ktest::miri_main` (in Nightly builds, run with -Z macro-backtrace for more info)\n```",
